      <section eId="sec_6_3_2">
        <num>6-3.2</num>
        <heading>Kinds of future estates</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_6_3_2__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Future estates are divided into:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_6_3_2__subsec_a__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Estates left in the creator, consisting of:\n  (A)  Reversions.\n  (B)  Possibilities of reverter.\n  (C)  Rights of reacquisition.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_6_3_2__subsec_a__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Estates in favor of a person other than the creator, namely\nremainders, that are:\n  (A)  Indefeasibly vested.\n  (B)  Vested subject to open.\n  (C)  Vested subject to complete defeasance.\n  (D)  Subject to a condition precedent.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
      </section>
